Please apply through this link: <a href="http://smrtr.io/jEn2CA" rel="nofollow">http://smrtr.io/jEn2CA</a><br>
<br>
BUSINESS OVERVIEW:<br>
At YMT Vacations, the goal is to provide our guests with affordable vacations they will remember for years to come. We assemble hotel, tour, sightseeing, and cruise components and offer a range of inclusive value-priced escorted tour and cruise/tour vacation packages throughout North America and worldwide. We sell direct to customers from sales offices in Los Angeles and Detroit. <br>
<br>
YMT Vacations is a member of Travelopia, which is the world's largest collection of specialist travel brands. Each brand is individually operated, creating unique experiences that are centered around specific destinations, passions or interests.<br>
<br>
POSITION SUMMARY:<br>
The Operations and Guest Experience Manager is responsible for the overall guest experience of YMT Vacations tours in the Hawaiian Islands.  This includes the execution of our tour programs along with the commercial performance of the optional tour program.  YMT operates fixed itinerary group tours year-round including a 13 day/4 island tour and a 12-day cruise tour typically sized between 40 and 120 guests with up to three group arrivals per week.  Reporting to the Los Angeles headquarters, this is a highly autonomous role with a high level of responsibility.  The successful candidate must be able to work under pressure, be adaptable and work on their own initiative.<br>
<br>
RESPONSIBILITIES:<br>
Operational Delivery<br>
•	Ensure timely and accurate pre-tour planning and administration<br>
•	Own and oversee day- to-day operations of over-the-road tour groups<br>
•	Play the lead role in vendor management and relationships - transportation, hotels, attractions and others<br>
•	Manage the Assistant Operations and Guest Experience Manager, Tour Directors and part-time guest facing staff <br>
•	Create, define and maintain operational on-tour standards and processes to ensure that YMT tours provide an exceptional guest experience<br>
•	Design and maintain very detailed and comprehensive tour technical itineraries<br>
•	Schedule, train, supervise and manage performance of YMT Tour Directors<br>
•	Travel regularly throughout the islands to appraise tour and vendor performance<br>
•	Respond to operational emergencies<br>
•	Assist as necessary in tour operations, deliver guest experience<br>
<br>
Optional Tours<br>
•	Responsible for achieving YMT's optional tour sales targets and profitability<br>
•	Design optional tour programs, negotiate terms and conditions with suppliers<br>
•	Manage the sales process, design and implement sales process and tactics to ensure that optional tour sales and margins are optimized<br>
•	Manage accounting administration of optional tours and report to YMT Los Angeles office on a regular basis<br>
<br>
SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE<br>
•	Prior relevant Hawaii based tourism management experience in a guest facing role is required, including destination management, operational hotel management, event management or tour operations<br>
•	Minimum of two years of staff management required<br>
•	Excellent analytical and communication skills, both verbal and written <br>
•	Vendor negotiation and management a plus<br>
•	Must possess innovative and creative thinking skills to "think out of the box". <br>
•	Must have a basic understanding of finance including budgeting and basic accounts administration<br>
•	Must be a team player with the ability to work with a multitude of departments and staff members of all levels, including senior executives<br>
•	Requires strong interpersonal skills and ability to problem solve, and work under pressure of immediate deadlines<br>
•	Strong working knowledge of MS Office and excellent time management skills<br>
•	Must be able to travel throughout the islands as required and occasionally work weekends (approximately 85% of time in office, 15% of time on tour)<br>
<br>
WORKING CONDITIONS:<br>
Duties and responsibilities are generally performed in an office environment with a regular work schedule.   Environmental conditions generally include ambient to cool inside temperature, ambient inside lighting and ambient inside low noise levels.  Physical demands generally include frequent reaching and grasping, light to moderate lifting (10-20 lbs.), and light to moderate carrying.  Mobility demands generally include continuous sitting and occasional standing.  Sensory demands generally include keyboarding, computer terminal, and telephone operation.<br>
<br>
PHYSICAL DEMANDS:  <br>
&#61607;	Walking, bending, pushing, reaching and lifting up to 50 lbs. (additional weight may be required with assistance) <br>
&#61607;	May be required to sit for long duration periods<br>
<br>
ENVIRONMENT AND SCOPE:<br>
This incumbent has a high degree of autonomy over own work load.  Must keep a professional demeanour at all times when representing the company. <br>
<br>
Disclaimer: The above information on this description has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities, and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job. Management reserves the right to add to or modify the duties and/or responsibilities of the Manager.<br>
<br>
Please apply through this link: <a href="http://smrtr.io/jEn2CA" rel="nofollow">http://smrtr.io/jEn2CA</a>    </section>

